				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Breaking Charm<a name="35814"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Apr 21 04 4:41 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I really highly recommend the ring as well, if you have some time to camp it and are on a low budget.  Currently, I'm swarming flies in PoD and have no real issues using it.  Be sure you have a pet window while swarming so you can see health as you target yourself.  I have my keys mapped like this:  w for ring, ` to toggle between last two targets, and f1 to target self.  I use w simply because I use the key often as my wizard, so it's convenient for me.  Charm pet, target victim, pet attack, hit f1 twice to re-target pet, as soon as the pet begins to get eaten, hit f1 to target self, w to break charm, then ` to target pet again.
<br />

<br />
Sounds complex, but once you get the rhythm down, it's no issue.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
